    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A deep red natural colorant made from secretions of the larvae of the lac insect. Lac dye is a byproduct produced during the shellac purification process; its primary colorant is laccaic acid. It was an important dyestuff used since ancient times, giving a lightfast tint to silk and wool, similar in color to dyes obtained from cochineal and kermes. Now synthetic colorants have replaced the use of lac dye.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
